# Phase 1: Analyze the Fix

This is a patch for VectorCombine:

[VectorCombine] Consolidate fragmented loads into wide loads
LLVM currently maintains multiple narrow loads (e.g., <2 x double>
or scalars) from adjacent memory addresses when they are combined
into a single larger vector (e.g., <4 x double>) through a sequence
of nested shufflevector instructions. These fragmented loads and the
associated shuffle tree remain as separate operations in the IR.

This patch introduces foldFragmentedLoads to identify these
fragmented load patterns within shuffle chains and consolidate them
into one or two wide loads that fit within the target's maximum
vector register width. The entire shuffle tree is folded into a
single shufflevector operation using the newly created wide load(s)
as operands.

Proof: https://alive2.llvm.org/ce/z/eZXjhM
Fixed: https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/140234

